      },
      "rationale": "The constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening) was selected based on published Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupon data and prior FDA FEA validation studies. Frictional contact at the screw-rod interface was confirmed to capture the dominant nonlinearity (rod slip at ~60% of yield force). Gradation 3 reflects physics-motivated model form selection with experimental corroboration of the dominant mechanism."
