        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Equivalency of input parameters acceptance criteria",
        "description": "FEA boundary conditions (fixture geometry, load application point, displacement rate) match ASTM F1717 test setup within documented tolerances. CMM-measured screw geometry used directly in FEA mesh generation."
      },
      "rationale": "The FEA model boundary conditions were constructed to replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry using CMM-measured fixture dimensions. Load application point, support span, and displacement rate were matched to the experimental protocol. Screw and rod geometry in the FEA mesh were derived from the same CMM measurements used to characterize the physical test samples, ensuring strong equivalency between simulation inputs and physical test conditions. Gradation 3 reflects direct geometric traceability between test and simulation."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-oc",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
