        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Output comparison acceptance criteria",
        "description": "Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm). Percent difference |FEA − mean(experiment)| / mean(experiment) < 10% for each QoI."
      },
      "rationale": "The area validation metric (E/uval) was computed for each QoI using ASME V&V 20 methodology. Results: stiffness E/uval=0.84, yield force E/uval=1.12, force at 40 mm E/uval=0.97 — all below the 1.96 threshold. Percent differences were 4.2%, 7.8%, and 5.1% respectively, all within the 10% acceptance bound. Gradation 3 reflects quantitative comparison with uncertainty-informed validation metrics."
