        "description": "QoIs (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the same metrics specified in ASTM F1717 and in the 510(k) submission performance testing requirements."
      },
      "rationale": "The three QoIs selected for validation (construct stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are identical to the performance metrics required by ASTM F1717 and referenced in the FDA guidance for spinal implant 510(k) submissions. These QoIs directly characterize the mechanical behavior relevant to clinical performance (construct rigidity and failure mode). Gradation 3 reflects direct alignment between validation QoIs and regulatory performance requirements."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/factor/nagaraja-cou1-rva",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "rationale": "The 'Relevance of the validation activities to the COU' factor is intended to assess how well the validation scenario represents a COU that differs from the validation scenario — i.e., when validation is performed in a surrogate or analogous context and extrapolation to the true COU is required. In this assessment, the validation activity IS the COU: the FEA model is being validated directly against ASTM F1717 bench testing of the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under the identical loading condition. There is no extrapolation from a surrogate validation context to a separate COU; accordingly, this factor does not introduce a meaningful credibility dimension and is designated not-applicable per ASME V&V 40 §6.3."
    }
